tract","Corticobulbar tract","Tectospinal tract"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Elateral corticospinal tract\u003C/strong\u003E serves as the principal motor pathway for voluntary movement control. Beginning in the motor cortex, these nerve fibres cross sides at the medullary pyramids and travel down the lateral portion of the spinal cord to enable precise control of muscles on the opposite side of the body.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlternative pathways serve different functions:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eanterior corticospinal tract\u003C/strong\u003E comprises a smaller proportion of motor fibres and primarily controls core body muscles\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Erubrospinal tract\u003C/strong\u003E, part of the extrapyramidal system, plays a less significant role in human motor control\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ecorticobulbar tract\u003C/strong\u003E specifically controls muscles of the head and neck via cranial nerves\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Etectospinal tract\u003C/strong\u003E helps coordinate neck and head movements in response to sensory input\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis lateral pathway enables sophisticated voluntary movements, particularly important for precise control of hands and feet.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The lateral corticospinal tract provides the main descending motor pathway for precise control of voluntary movements in the limbs and trunk.","Most corticospinal fibres cross to the opposite side at the medullary decussation before descending in the spinal cord.","The lateral tract carries most motor fibres (80-90%), while the anterior corticospinal tract contains the remainder."],"references":["Javed K, Reddy V, Lui F. Neuroanatomy, Lateral Corticospinal Tract. [Updated 2023 Jul 24]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK534818/","Smith AC, Weber KA 2nd, O\u0027Dell DR, Parrish TB, Wasielewski M, Elliott JM. Lateral Corticospinal Tract Damage Correlates With Motor Output in Incomplete Spinal Cord Injury. Arch Phys Med Rehabil. 2018 Apr;99(4):660-666. doi: 10.1016/j.apmr.2017.10.002. Epub 2017 Oct 26. PMID: 29107041; PMCID: PMC5871547.","Hall, J. E., \u0026 Hall, M. E. (2020). Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology E-Book: Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Singh, V. (2024).\u00a0Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022).\u00a0The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60257"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16515"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60257","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60257"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-26T23:07:23+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-26T23:08:09+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9206"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74771"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medic